# 📊 Installing Metrics Server Using Helm

The **Metrics Server** collects resource usage data from Kubernetes nodes and pods.

It enables the following commands:

```
kubectl top pods
kubectl top nodes
```

---

### Check existing Helm repositories

```
helm repo ls
```

---

### Add Metrics Server Repository

```
helm repo add metrics-server https://kubernetes-sigs.github.io/metrics-server/
```

---

### Install Metrics Server

```
helm upgrade --install metrics-server metrics-server/metrics-server
```

---

### Verify Installation

```
helm list
```

Check metrics:

```
kubectl top pods
kubectl top nodes
```

---

### Delete Release

```
helm delete metrics-server
```

